Files:
- plugins/clickup/src/clickup-api.ts (save OrigSend at module level, export resetWsInterceptor)
- plugins/clickup/src/index.ts (add teardown() method)

Context:
Current installWsInterceptor() (lines 40-66):
  const installWsInterceptor = (): void => {
    const g = globalThis as Record<string, unknown>;
    if (g.__cu_ws_interceptor_installed) return;
    g.__cu_ws_interceptor_installed = true;

    const OrigSend = WebSocket.prototype.send; // LOCAL variable — not accessible from outside
    WebSocket.prototype.send = function (data) {
      // intercepts JSON auth frames to capture JWT and teamId
      return OrigSend.call(this, data);
    };
  };
  installWsInterceptor(); // called at module load

The OrigSend is a local variable inside the function closure. It needs to be elevated to module level.

Fix:
1. In clickup-api.ts, add a module-level variable: `let origWsSend: typeof WebSocket.prototype.send | null = null;`
2. In installWsInterceptor(), save the original: `origWsSend = WebSocket.prototype.send;` BEFORE overwriting
3. Export a new function `resetWsInterceptor()` that:
   - Restores WebSocket.prototype.send from origWsSend (if set)
   - Sets (globalThis as any).__cu_ws_interceptor_installed = false
   - Sets origWsSend = null
4. In index.ts, add teardown() that calls resetWsInterceptor()

Constraints:
- Do NOT change the JWT/teamId capture logic in the interceptor
- resetWsInterceptor() must be a no-op if origWsSend is null (interceptor was never installed)
- The __cu_ws_interceptor_installed guard must be reset so re-injection after teardown correctly re-installs the interceptor
